+# Spec [[cat001]] [[cat003]] [[board]]
+
+## problem
+
+We need to authenticate users coming in via an external partner
+integration using SAML SSO. Today the only shared auth capability is
+[[ft001|basic-auth (password+TOTP)]], whose `## providing` section
+explicitly scopes it to password+TOTP and lists *"No SSO, no SAML, no
+OAuth"* as non-goals.
+
+[[adr0001|All services authenticate via ft001 basic-auth]] anticipated
+this exact case: *"External SSO would require a new feature, not
+extending ft001."* Extending `ft001` to also speak SAML would widen
+its contract from "internal humans with a password" to "any external
+IdP federation," conflating two different trust domains and breaking
+the existing contract its current consumers rely on.
+
+So the right shape is a **new sibling [[cat001|security]] Feature**
+(`ft###` to be minted at the `spec` stage) providing SAML SP
+functionality, sitting next to `ft001` rather than replacing or
+subsuming it. Services that need SAML opt in; services that don't
+keep using `ft001` unchanged.
+
+**Concrete drivers.**
+
+- A new external partner integration needs to federate identity from
+  their IdP — they cannot provision per-user passwords in our `users`
+  table, and they require SAML specifically (not OIDC).
+- The partner-facing surface will live in the `auth` service (see
+  `src/services/auth/`), which already owns `ft001`'s session
+  bridging — same service, new code path.
+- `ft001`'s consumers (auth, reports, metrics) should be untouched by
+  this work; the new feature must coexist, not refactor existing
+  callers.
+
+**Out of scope for this spec.**
+
+- Choosing the SAML library / IdP-side configuration — defer to
+  `## solution` at the spec stage.
+- Designing the cross-feature session bridge (does a SAML-authenticated
+  user share `ft001`'s Redis sessions, or get its own?) — flagged here
+  but resolved at spec stage with an ADR if the answer constrains
+  future Implementations.
+- Any UI work in the `reports` service — partner traffic terminates at
+  the `auth` service for this milestone.
+
+**Open questions to resolve at `spec` stage.**
+
+- Is one Feature sufficient, or do we need a generic `federated-auth`
+  Feature with SAML as the first protocol and OIDC as a planned
+  successor? (Cheapest now: SAML-only Feature; widen later via a new
+  Feature if OIDC arrives.)
+- Does this trigger a *new* ADR superseding or extending [[adr0001]]
+  to read "services authenticate via ft001 *or* ft### (SAML)"? Likely
+  yes — capture during spec-writing.
+- Where does the SP metadata / IdP trust config live — Vault
+  ([[ft002|vault-secrets]]) or a new config surface? Vault is the
+  obvious answer; confirm at spec stage.
+
+## consumers (provisional)
+
+- `src/services/auth/` — primary consumer; partner SSO terminates here.
+- (future) any service that the partner needs to reach directly —
+  none planned in this milestone; will go via the auth service first.
+
